explanation: The Trie data structure is used to efficiently store and retrieve strings. Each node in the Trie contains a dictionary of its children and a boolean indicating whether it is the end of a word. The insert operation iterates through each character in the word, creating new nodes as necessary. The search and startsWith operations iterate through each character in the word or prefix, returning False if a character is not found in the Trie.

